output.sentences: So I went to a place with all these weird paintings on the wall.
One of them was of the well loved man Frederick Douglass.
A lot of the paintings were mourning war and encouraging peace.
The painted murals and buildings were everywhere.
I could see how hard it had been for the families of people who died in the war, and how much they must be missed.
